<HEAD>Where to Send Hugo Donations</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Hugo Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Relief efforts for victims of Hurricane Hugo in
Puerto Rico are being coordinated by the Department of Puerto Rican
Community Affairs in the United States, 304 Park Ave. South, New
York, N.Y. 10010.
   Its hot line for people wishing to donate money is: (212)
473-4788.
   In addition, the federal Interior Department has established a
24-hour telephone number for people seeking information about the
situation in the Virgin Islands. The number is 202-343-6816.
   There are two American Red Cross numbers for callers who wish to
pledge money for Puerto Rican hurricane relief: (800) 453-9000 for
English speakers, and (800) 453-4487 for Spanish speakers.
   Checks can be sent to the American Red Cross in Greater New York,
P.O. Box 4691, Grand Central Station, New York, N.Y. 10164.
   Donations can be made at all area branches of Banco Popular de
Puerto Rico, Banco De Ponce and Manufacturers Hanover Trust, which
have set up special disaster relief accounts.
   The federal Interior Department has established a 24-hour
telephone number for people seeking information about the situation
in the Virgin Islands. The number is 202-343-6816.
   Other organizations handling donations are:
   Ayuda Pro-Damnificados, Huracan Hugo-Puerto Rico, P.O. Box 674,
New York, N.Y. 10010;
   United Nations Disaster Relief Office, Re: Hurricane Hugo, Room
2395, Secretariat Building, One U.N. Plaza, New York, N.Y. 10037;
   Caribbean Action Lobby Relief Organization. 391 Eastern Parkway,
Brooklyn, N.Y. 11216.
   Hurricane Fund - Save the Children, P.O. Box 970, Westport, Conn.
06881.
</TEXT>
